<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COLORADO PROVIDED RICHARD SOME ADDED MOTIVATION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Gary Barnett has replaced Rick Neuheisel as coach
at Colorado, but that won't make USC cornerback Kris Richard feel
any fonder of the Buffaloes.
</P>
<P>
   Richard is sore that Colorado, under Neuheisel, refused to
recruit him as a senior at Serra High in Gardena.
</P>
<P>
   ``They told me I wasn't the kind of player that they needed in
their system,'' Richard said. ``I wasn't good enough to be a
Colorado Buffalo. I still remember that.
</P>
<P>
   ``. . . I still remember the letter.''
</P>
<P>
   Since Antuan Simmons is out for the season following surgery to
remove a tumor, Richard has become the secondary's mainstay, firmly
entrenched at left cornerback while Darrell Rideaux and Chris Cash
split time at right cornerback.
</P>
<P>
   It's a complete turnabout from last season, when Richard was
considered the weak link because of his inexperience.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's kind of crazy,'' Richard said of his lofty new status.
``But would it be this way if Antuan was still here? I say to
myself, 'If Antuan was still here, who would they be trying to
question then?' ''
</P>
<P>
   __ McGuire out: Offensive tackle Joe McGuire said he probably
wouldn't play against Colorado. He's bothered by a compressed disc
in his back and doesn't know how long he might be out.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's feeling better, but I'm day to day,'' McGuire said.
</P>
<P>
   With McGuire unable to play, Jacob Rogers, Eric Torres and
Phillip Eaves are the candidates to play in USC's goal-line
offense, in which starting right tackle Faaesea Mailo moves to
fullback.
</P>
<P>
   __ MacKenzie struggles: Hackett said tailback Malaefou
MacKenzie, who has been bothered by a sore hamstring, was ``a
little iffy'' during Wednesday's practice and he might not play
against Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wasn't comfortable with how he looked,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Petros Papadakis, who was sick Tuesday, returned and could back
up starter Sultan McCullough, with freshman Chris Howard also
available. Howard's availability is limited because of his slow
recovery from offseason knee surgery.
</P>
<P>
   __ Kelly theory: Wide receiver Kareem Kelly doesn't think USC
will be complacent after having a week off and offered his own
analogy for how the Trojans would remain sharp.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're the hunters. We've got to go out and hunt our food,''
Kelly said. ``We're not going to take anyone lightly.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Add Kelly: In the wake of Penn State's 24-7 loss to Toledo,
Kelly believes USC could have ruined the Nittany Lions' confidence
with their sound victory in the Kickoff Classic.
</P>
<P>
   ``By beating them, we probably threw them off and messed up
their season,'' Kelly said.
</P>
<P>
   The downside, Kelly believes, is that USC's win over the Nittany
Lions has been downgraded.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everyone's going to think our Penn State victory was a
fluke,'' Kelly said. ``But it's up to us to change the mind of the
critics now.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Grootegoed update: Test results should be available today on
strong safety Matt Grootegoed, who is believed to have
mononucleosis. He is sitting out this week and will probably miss
next week's practices.
</P>
<P>
   Because of the improved depth in the secondary, no players will
need to be shifted around to replace Grootegoed. DeShaun Hill will
continue to backup starter Troy Polamalu.
</P>
<P>
   ``Losing Matt is not going to cripple us,'' secondary coach
Dennis Thurman said. ``Last year, it would have crippled us.''
</P>
</TEXT>
