<P>
   SCI-INDIANS-CANNIBALS (Undated) _ Scientists have found what
they say is the first direct evidence of cannibalism among
prehistoric Indians in the American Southwest, belying the image of
these people as steadfastly peaceful farmers, perhaps reigniting a
smoldering controversy over whether ancestral Indians ever made it
a practice to eat human flesh. By John Noble Wilford. 1,200 words.
</P>
