<P>
   REVIEW-BETTY _ ``Nurse Betty,'' the great new Neil Labute movie
starring Renee Zellweger, Morgan Freeman, Greg Kinnear, and Chris
Rock. (Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-NURSEBETTY _ The joys of ``Nurse Betty'' are its yin and
yang of abrupt Quentin Tarantino violence
</P>
<P>
   and philosophy-spouting bad guys, mixed with the innocent
optimism of Frank Capra. The surprise is that this
audience-friendly juggling act comes from irector Neil LaBute,
previously known for such nasty misogynistic films as In the
``Company of Men'' and ``Your Friends and Neighbors.'' The last
thing you would expect from him is an Oz-like odyssey with such a
radiant, albeit delusional, Dorothy Gale. Three and one-half stars.
(Erstein, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-GUN _ ``The Way of the Gun.'' Not so good action flick.
(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   KEMPNER-GREENBERG _ Interview with documentary filmmaker Aviva
Kempner, director of ``The Life and Times of Hank Greenberg.''
(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-LOVE-SEX _ Movie review: ``Love and Sex.'' (Ringel,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-ASUNDER - A marriage put asunder doesn't just come apart;
it explodes, flinging shrapnel that rips through souls. That's what
director Tim Reid's film''Asunder'' attempts to depict: an
emotional explosion that rips through two couples who initially
appear to have everything. And while ``Asunder'' has its moments,
its laborious pacing, uneven acting and often weak dialogue keep it
from being anything but average. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   TV-SOLE-SURVIVOR _ Dean Koontz's ``Sole Survivor'' is a
thoroughly gripping four-hour miniseries. In fact, it's one of the
best miniseries I've seen in some time. Not many four-hour movies
can command my attention from start to finish. But it's also
somewhat disturbing and,
</P>
<P>
   at times, difficult to watch. Dean Koontz's ``Sole Survivor''
airs Wednesday and Thursday on Fox. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
