   JUDGES-ELECT (Undated) _ In a year when election contests for
state judgeships around the country have become more baldly
political than ever before, the chief justices of 15 states are
planning an unusual summit meeting to try to limit what some of
them say are widespread election abuses that threaten public
confidence in the courts. By William Glaberson.
