abuses in the Louisiana juvenile prison system. The agreement is
expected to limit the use of force and increase monitoring,
education and mental health care. By Fox Butterfield.
</P>
<P>
   JEWS-CHRISTIANS (Undated) _ Nearly 200 U.S. rabbis are about to
issue a theological statement calling on Jews to re-evaluate how
they perceive Christianity and Christian people. It says that
Nazism was not a Christian phenomenon, and that Jews should not
blame contemporary Christians for the sins of their ancestors. The
rabbis who signed are Reform, Conservative, Reconstructionist and
Orthodox. By Laurie Goodstein.
</P>
