Convention, second only to promises to protect abortion rights and
overhaul the health care system. The minimum wage issue is so
popular that congressional Republicans dare not oppose it outright.
Instead they are loading it up with tax breaks for business. George
W. Bush has his own zinger. He wants to give states the right to
ignore the minimum wage if they want. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
