   CLINTON-UN _ NEW YORK _ President seizes the opporunity at this
largest-ever gathering of world leaders to hold a series of
bilateral meetings. Key among them today will be with China's Jiang
Zemin, who should be more cordial following last week's decision by
Clinton to leave the controversial National Missile Defense system
for his successor to deal with. Developing. (Deans, Cox News
Service)
</P>
