   OPED/EDITORIALBORDERS-COLUMN _ T.S. Eliot wrote that April was
the cruelest month. He never visited Texas in August. One joke
going around is that the devil was thinking about moving hell to
Texas but decided it was too hot. (Borders, Nacogdoches Daily
Sentinel) MOVEDLATHAM-COLUMN _ MARSHALL, Texas _ You hear a great
deal about global warming these days. Some people say it threatens
life on Earth, others say it is nothing but a myth. Me, I don't
know anything about that either way.
