   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-GASPRICES _ LONDON _ A stranglehold on refineries and
oil-storage areas by truck drivers and farmers led to widespread
shortages of gasoline and rationing in some areas of France on
Tuesday, and the unrest over the high cost of diesel fuel appeared
set to spread to Belgium and Spain. Gasoline has exceeded $6.50 a
gallon across Europe and people are really angry. Additionally, the
French strikes are screwing up life on this side of the channel.
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service) WITH PHOTO and TEXT DATA
</P>
