Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-ASUNDER - A marriage put asunder doesn't just come apart;
it explodes, flinging shrapnel that rips through souls. That's what
director Tim Reid's film''Asunder'' attempts to depict: an
emotional explosion that rips through two couples who initially
appear to have everything. And while ``Asunder'' has its moments,
its laborious pacing, uneven acting and often weak dialogue keep it
from being anything but average. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   TV-SOLE-SURVIVOR _ Dean Koontz's ``Sole Survivor'' is a
thoroughly gripping four-hour miniseries. In fact, it's one of the
best miniseries I've seen in some time. Not many four-hour movies
can command my attention from start to finish. But it's also
somewhat disturbing and,
</P>
<P>
   at times, difficult to watch. Dean Koontz's ``Sole Survivor''
airs Wednesday and Thursday on Fox. (Thompson, Palm Beach
Post)SPORTS
