<P>
   MITSUBISHI (Normal, Ill.) _ For a short but trying time a few
years ago, this small town made national headlines. Horrifying
stories had emerged about the Mitsubishi auto assembly plant here.
Its factory floor, some workers charged, was one where some men
felt free to grope female workers, to ask them to bare their
breasts or to aim air guns between their legs. The company, while
vehemently denying the charges, nevertheless agreed in June 1998 to
pay a record $34 million to settle the largest federal lawsuit over
sexual harassment. In reality, however, while the headlines have
faded, the problems have not. By Reed Abelson.
</P>
