<P>
   MAYAN RIVIERA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TANKAH, Mexico _ From the most developed beach resorts in Mexico
to some of the most rustic, the Mayan Riviera _ an 80-mile coastal
stretch from Cancun to Tulum, south of Akumal _ has it all.
Everywhere, you get great beaches, uniformly sunny weather, fresh
seafood and beautiful sunsets. What differs along the coast is the
level of service (armies of waiters and bellhops vs. grab your own
beer from the cooler) and the amenities (whirlpool tubs and
designer furniture vs. rooms cooled by breezes only). We spend four
days along the coast, reporting in from four very different beach
spots. By PATRICIA RODRIGUEZ. Story will move in ``t'' travel
category. (Accompanied by RIVIERA-IF YOU GO.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
</P>
