<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CANCER-DRUG (Undated) _ Researchers in Holland are
questioning the safety of a practice that has been widely endorsed
by cancer experts in the United States: prescribing the drug
tamoxifen to prevent breast cancer in women who are healthy but at
high risk for the disease. The new doubts about the drug are based
on a study of more than 1,000 women, reported in the British
journal The Lancet, showing that women taking tamoxifen had a
greater risk than previously reported of dying from endometrial
cancer, which affects the lining of the uterus. By Denise Grady.
</P>
