<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With TECH-CAMPUS. For release Sunday, Sept. 10
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Some of the features at or near Sun Microsystems' new Santa
Clara, Calif., campus, formerly the site of a mental hospital.
</P>
<P>
   _ Four restored historic buildings, including a clock tower, an
auditorium and the former hospital director's home. Three of the
buildings are open to the public for concerts, meetings and other
events.
</P>
<P>
   _ A 15-acre park dedicated to Santa Clara by Sun and maintained
by the city.
</P>
<P>
   _ A cemetery that holds the remains of 112 people killed when an
earthquake struck near the hospital in 1906.
</P>
<P>
   _ An emergency homeless shelter, donated by Sun to non-profit
groups.
</P>
<P>
   _ 450 hardwood and palm trees.
</P>
