<P>
   LEOFRANK-RABBI _ ATLANTA _ The Cobb County rabbi who placed a
memorial at the spot of Leo Frank's lynching has taken up the cause
again. Rabbi Steven Lebow has written a letter to the NFL
complaining about comments local attorney Tom Watson Brown made in
a recent AJC story alleging that ``the Jews bribed the governor''
into commuting Frank's sentence. Brown is a part owner of the
Falcons. The rabbi says Brown's comments are anti-Semitic and he
likens Brown to Marge Schott. Brown is a descendant of Tom
</P>
<P>
   Watson, whose racist rhetoric fueled the lynchers in 1915. Brown
isn't apologizing, but explains his comments. (Visser, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
