<P>
   SAMSUNG _ AUSTIN, Texas _ South Korea's Samsung Electronics Co.
says it expects the shortage of the most common computer memory
chips will last for at least another two years, and it intends to
keep spending heavilyon adding manufacturing capacity. Samsung's
announcement opens the door to a potential expansion of its sizable
presence in Austin, where the company employs 1,100 people. Samsung
spokesman Bill Cryer said this week he expects the Korean company
will decide sometime in the next year whether it will build a
second factory in Northeast Austin anytime soon. When it first
announced its expansion in Austin, Samsung officials said the
company might build up to five chip factories here, depending upon
the continued strength of the market. (Ladendorf, Austin
American-Statesman)
