get forecasts enhanced through new computer technology. An
automated, short-term forecast tool developed at the National
Center for Atmospheric Research will predict the birth, growth, and
decay of Sydney-area thunderstorms every five minutes during the
Olympics. The experiment will test how much of a boost automated
tools can provide to human forecasters.
