<P>
   CAMPAIGN-ROUNDUP (Undated) _ George W. Bush, moving to address
some Republican worries that his campaign is faltering, flanks
himself with military heroes of the Persian Gulf War as he pledges
to equip America's armed forces with billions of dollars worth of
new high-tech gear. Al Gore, buoyed by a new poll showing him with
a 6-point edge over Bush, is endorsed by the 1.5-million-member
Teamsters union. By STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
