<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
story for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Friday, Sept. 8, and thereafter. For questions, contact Michael
McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   FEAR-FEAR (Los Angeles) _ If the criminals don't get you, the
fear of them will, according to a trio of clinical psychologists at
California State University, Northridge. Following a statewide
study, the researchers have identified a crime fear syndrome that
results in chronic underlying feelings of alienation, depression,
anger and anxiety. More criminals are in prison, more cops are on
the street, but we still buy guns and move into walled-in
communities. By Erik Nelson. (Will also move in the ``a'' national
news file.)
