<HEADER>
A5476 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-FBN-NFLCAPSULES-TEX     09-07 2224
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-NFL </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WEEK 2 NFL CAPSULES
</HEADLINE>
 CAPSULES-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By Stephen Schroats 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
CHICAGO BEARS at TAMPA BAY BUCCANEERS 
WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS: Bears 0-1, Buccaneers 1-0 SERIES: Bears
lead, 30-14 LAST REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Buccaneers won, 20-6, on
Jan. 2, 2000, as QB Shaun King passes for 178 yards and one TD,
giving Tampa Bay its first division title since 1981. THE LINE:
Buccaneers by 7 THE SCOOP
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ For the second consecutive week, Bears QB Cade McNown faces
another member of the draft class of 1999. Last week it was Vikings
QB Daunte Culpepper. This week it is Bucs QB Shaun King.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Bucs have won four in a row vs. NFC Central foes and
allowed a combined 49 points in those games.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Bucs have held the Bears to fewer than 20 points in their
past eight meetings.
</P>
<P>
