<HEADER>
A5560 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a BC-SHUTTLE0908-COX     09-07 0301
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHUTTLE0908-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Launch tickets sold on Internet
 &HT;    By Brian D. Crecente
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. _ It took a while, but the Kennedy Space Center
finally went high tech.
</P>
<P>
   You can now go online to buy space shuttle launch tickets.
</P>
<P>
   In the past, space buffs had to show up at the visitor complex
no earlier than five to seven days ahead of a launch to buy
tickets, said Michelle Salyer, public relations manager for the
Kennedy Space Center Visitor Complex.
</P>
<P>
   A couple from Switzerland was the first to buy tickets for
today's scheduled 8:45 a.m. launch shortly after online sales began
Aug. 15.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's so much easier to plan your vacation around the launch
now,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   The 5,000 tickets to today's launch sold out Tuesday, she said,
but plenty of tickets remain for the Oct. 5 and Nov. 30 launches. A
basic ticket sells for $15, while the maximum access ticket sells
for $34.50 and comes with lots of extra goodies.
</P>
<P>
   If you're planning to go, bring a lawn chair or blanket, but no
food or drinks are allowed, Salyer said.
</P>
<P>
   The viewing area is about 6 miles from the launch pad, Salyer
said, miles closer than the free public viewing areas.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can definitely hear the launch,'' she said. ``It's
tremendously loud.''
</P>
<P>
   Of course buying tickets doesn't guarantee you will see a
launch; after all, this is rocket science.
</P>
<P>
   If the mission is delayed or scrubbed before you get to the
viewing area, you can just come back for the mission's next launch
attempt, she said. But if the mission is delayed after you get to
the viewing area, you're out of luck.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are selling a launch viewing opportunity,'' she said. ``We
are the real thing here.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-07-00 2141EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
