   (NYT16) BOSTON -- Sept. 7, 2000 -- AUTHOR-GARMENT-BOS -- He is
the great mystery man of political scandal, the shadowiest figure
in the annals of journalism: Deep Throat, the secret source who
helped lead Washington Post reporters Bob Woodward and Carl
Bernstein to the truth about Watergate in 1972 and 1973. Only four
people know his identity: Woodward, Bernstein, retired Post
executive editor Ben Bradlee, and, of course, Deep Throat himself.
Leonard Garment thinks he can make it five. In his new book, ``In
Search of Deep Throat,'' Garment names John P. Sears as his man.
Garment during an interview about his book in August. (Tom
Landers/The Boston Globe) LITE
