Annapolis is the United States Naval Academy. To architecture
lovers, it is a charming 18th-century town built on a late
17th-century Baroque street plan. Annapolis from the waterfront at
the City Dock looking up over the town's low skyline to the Baroque
dome of the Maryland State House. (Justin Lane/The New York Times)
