   (NYT31) HOUSTON -- Sept. 6, 2000 -- FRIENDSHIP-HNS -- For much
of her life, writer Sandy Sheehy was terrible at making and keeping
friends. It wasn't until she was in her mid-30s that Sheehy began
reaching out to other women and another decade before she
understood what it meant to be a good friend. A former Houstonian
who now lives in Galveston,
</P>
<P>
   Sheehy has authored two books, one that began her journey
entitled ``''Texas Rich,'' and her second book, ``Connecting: The
Enduring Power of Female Friendship'' (William Morrow, $25) which
in the process, she says, made her a better friend. (Betty
Tichich/The Houston Chronicle) Story moved on 08/30/00
