allegedly staged a robbery at the gas station where he worked. He
put tape over the lens of a surveillance camera, stashed $400 in a
trash bin out back and then called police. What tripped him up was
that when he covered the lens, he used transparent tape. By Richard
Espinoza. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   RIVER (Washington) _ The Senate voted today to prevent the Corps
of Engineers from raising the flow on the Missouri River in the
spring to help endangered wildlife. Many senators downstream,
including ours, were outraged by the idea that barges may not be
able to run and some farmers may lose some land back to the river.
But the administration and some upstream senators wanted the river
to be returned to a more natural flow. Because of the provision the
White House says it will veto the Interior department
appropriations bill. By Kevin Murphy. Story will move in the ``w''
category.
